# Rules for AI engineering / LLM pipeline work
# For ML/training projects, use python-ml-template instead

## Package name
- The package name is the folder under src/ — infer it from the directory structure
- Never assume it is "my_project"; check src/ and use whatever is there

## Dependencies
- Add new dependencies to pyproject.toml under [project] dependencies

## Config
- Secrets (.env / env vars) and non-secrets (config.yaml) are kept strictly separate
- Always access config through the settings singleton — import `settings` from the project's config module
- Secrets are str fields on Settings with no default, populated automatically from .env / env vars
- Non-secret values live in config.yaml and are accessed as nested attributes (e.g. settings.llm.default_model)
- Never call os.getenv() directly; never open or parse config.yaml manually
- config.py is the single bootstrap file — it handles both settings and logging setup

## Logging
- Call setup_logging() once at the top of main.py — import it from the project's config module
- Use get_logger(__name__) from config in every module, never use print()

## LLM calls
- All LLM calls go through src/<package>/services/llm_client.py
- llm_client.py implements the BaseLLMClient ABC defined in models/
- Use OpenRouter as the default provider via OpenAI-compatible API (openai package, custom base_url)
- Default model lives in config.yaml under llm.default_model — access it as settings.llm.default_model, never hardcode at call sites

## Data
- Use Pydantic BaseModel for all data passed between modules — no raw dicts
- All ABCs and shared interfaces are defined in models/ alongside Pydantic schemas

## Structure and design
- All external integrations (LLM, vector stores, embedders) sit in services/ and implement an ABC from models/
- services/ — anything that makes a network call or talks to an external system; always implements an ABC
- core/ — orchestration and pipeline logic (how and in what order services are called); no direct external calls
- utils/ — pure, stateless functions with no I/O (text chunking, prompt formatting, parsing); no imports from services/ or core/
- core/ and utils/ are added as the project grows — they do not exist in the bare template
- Bootstrap (settings + logging) → src/<package>/config.py
- Entry point → src/<package>/main.py

## Type safety
- Never use Any — if you don't know the type, stop and ask
- # type: ignore is a last resort: only permitted when the error originates from a known library typing gap (not your own code), must be scoped with the error code (# type: ignore[code], never bare # type: ignore), and must have a comment explaining why

## Verification
- After every non-trivial code change, run `make check` (ruff lint → pyright → pytest) and fix all errors before considering the task done
- Do NOT run make check after: editing README.md or other docs, changing only comments, changing config.yaml values without touching its schema
